Disturbance_note: The forest regenerated after the volcanic eruption of Mt. Tarumae in 1669 and 1739 , typhoons in 1954, 2004
Human usage of the forest has been restricted for the past 400 years

Although the forest is an old-growth forest, human disturbances such as fire, grazing, and selective cutting took place until 1930s at surrounding forests. Remains of charcoal making and selective cutting took place until 1930s at surrounding forests. Remains of charcoal making were found around the plot
A light selective cutting probably occurred because remains of charcoal making were found around the plot
